DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Term Search Criteria Keyword java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:A word or expression used for some particular thing.:An object that exists for defining the search parameters for a domain._A small set of words designed to convey the subject of a technical article._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
